- [Instructor] So why do we talk about change at all?

2
00:00:03.010 --> 00:00:05.060
Well, the new product development process

3
00:00:05.060 --> 00:00:09.060
is all about solving problems, and the changes are often

4
00:00:09.060 --> 00:00:11.060
the problem statements that the engineering

5
00:00:11.060 --> 00:00:13.090
and design professionals use as input

6
00:00:13.090 --> 00:00:15.090
for the design tasks.

7
00:00:15.090 --> 00:00:19.040
A change may describe some new intellectual property

8
00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:22.040
that has to be created, a new design that has

9
00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:26.000
to be created based on customer requirements, and so forth.

10
00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.090
Conversely, a change may arise from,

11
00:00:28.090 --> 00:00:31.050
shall we say, opportunities of a product

12
00:00:31.050 --> 00:00:34.090
that's not performing up to expectations in the field.

13
00:00:34.090 --> 00:00:37.030
Despite the fact that change is at the very core

14
00:00:37.030 --> 00:00:40.070
of engineering, it also elicits a lot of emotions

